{ Sooner or later this move is going to be played so I cover only this move order. }
5... Bg7 6. Be3
{ The main move for White. Our opponent might choose a few different setups from now and the move Be3 is useful in most of them. }
6... Rb8
{ As you could see in all lines in this chapter, this is the standard plan everywhere. That's why this line is so practical. }
