11. h3
{ Otherwise we would play ... h4. Now, it is not a good option because White will reply with g4. }
11... e6 12. Nc1
{ This is a standard way of preparing c3 without allowing any exchanges. }
12... Ne7 13. c3 Ndc6 { The disadvantage is that the pawn on c3 is a target. }
14. Ne2 a5 15. d4 Ba6
{ With this move Black threatens to take on c3 take on d4 take on e2 and then the d4-pawn falls. White has to do something ugly to defend against this threat. I find this chapter to be one of the most pleasant ones in the whole course. }
