{ 8.Bc4  O-O  9.O-O  e6  just transposes.   Note that White would love to solidify the centre with  8.d3 ??  but it runs into  8...Qa5+  ∓ }
8... O-O 9. Bc4 e6 { As I've mentioned, ... d5 is next. } 10. d3
{ 10.Bb3  is a smart move that discourages  10...d5  , but we will play it anyway!  11.e5  is White's point, but after  11...a5  12.a4  d3 !  we destroy White's pawn structure. After  13.cxd3  Nf5  Black has a large advantage. Our plan is to continue with ... Qb6+ followed by ... Nd4, completely paralysing White's queenside and planning ... f6, destroying White's centre. }
