{ This is the most characteristic approach, typical for the Rossolimo System. White gets a longterm pressure on our doubled c-pawns but we have a pair of Bishops. Resulting positions are of a double-edged character which should be a good sign for people who like to play for a win - us! Note that we will cover all of White's options connected with the move Bxc6 first, and only then we will see what happens after other moves. }
